Introduction

In December 2010, Co-ed School split into sub-groups, with the female members forming 5dolls, alongside new member Seo Eungyo. The group debuted in early 2011 with two promotional videos featuring Jay Park and released their first mini album in February. Despite gaining attention, they faced criticism for alleged lip-syncing during performances. In May, they released their second mini-album Time To Play. Internal conflicts emerged, leading to a bullying scandal that resulted in Chanmi and Soomi leaving the group. New members, including Han Nayeon, Shannon, and trainee Choi Jihyun, were added. In July 2013, the group rebranded as F-ve Dolls and released the digital single "Since 1971" with a revised lineup including Cho Seung-hee and Oh Yeon-kyung.

F-ve Dolls continued promotions with the mini-album "First Love" in September 2013, featuring the track Can You Love Me? with Kim Dani of T-ara N4, marking her debut. That same month, they also released alternate versions of "Can You Love Me?" and the music video for 'Deceive'. In late 2014, disbandment rumors began when the group was removed from their label's official website. The label confirmed the disbandment on March 10, 2015, stating that remaining contracted members would be part of a new group. Later that year, member Cho Seunghee re-debuted with the group DIA, though she left in 2016.
